-- Australia shares close 0.8 pct higher as battered banks bounce
-- 
-- Wed Oct 01, 2014 02:24AM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, Oct 1 (Reuters) - Australian shares added 0.8 percent on Wednesday, supoorted by a rebound in recently battered banking stocks, though sentiment remained fragile on softer-than-expected retail sales data and weakness on Wall Street. [ID:nL3N0RV70G]

